#inline#mFMb_DS_SetAlarm( boolean {; idleMode } )/*	What it does:	It sets an alarm flag for optional idle mode		Required parameters:	none, it wil set the alarm boolean for userNotIdle if no parameter is given		Optional parameters:	"userIdle", "userNotIdle", "scriptPaused", "scriptRunning" or "unSafe"		returns:		nothing if the syntax is correct, <?> if not 			1218 ( this number cannot be evaluated ) if the boolean flag is invalid			1224 (the function is not defined / calculation undefined ) if the idleMode string is incorrect			notes:		For more information, see the example file "Idle Modes".		see also:		mFMb_DS_GetAlarm( boolean {; idleMode } )*/